<item>
            <title>[LU-19779] ENOSPC observability to enable safe near-full OST utilization</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19779</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Lustre, filesystem &#8220;full&#8221; behavior is effectively driven by per-OST capacity. When an OST approaches 100% utilization, writes targeting that OST can fail with &lt;tt&gt;ENOSPC&lt;/tt&gt;, which often forces administrators to start deleting data early (commonly around ~98% OST usage) to avoid unpredictable job failures. On very large filesystems (e.g., tens of PB), this operational &#8220;fear margin&#8221; translates into substantial unusable capacity and cost inefficiency.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, when &lt;tt&gt;ENOSPC&lt;/tt&gt; occurs, operators often cannot quickly determine which file was involved, making incident response and policy decisions difficult. This lack of attribution/visibility is a major factor preventing confident near-full utilization.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
